The paper deals with question-answering on video contents, which involves both vision and language in real-world settings. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), or information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of deep learning models such as LSTM and attention also supports these sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.IR.
